&lt;p&gt;A bit over two years ago I wrote &lt;a href="http://milosophical.me/blog/2015/minecraft-python-0.html"&gt;a post about hacking minecraft with Python&lt;/a&gt;. During my holiday break this year I decided to revisit this, and have a bit more of a go with it.  Some things have changed, including the Minecraft Bukkit Server that I used then (CanaryMod) being abandoned, and some new enhanced modules that let you run Minecraft PI Python code on a non-PI machine, with Python 3!  So let's dig in.
